  "texts": [
    "By concatenating multiple groups of encoded embeddings, ICAE can handle up to 5,120 tokens.",
    "However, its compression ratio decreases compared to GIST.",
    "In addition, ICAE is trained and tested on the Pile dataset (Gao et al., 2020b), which may overlap with the training corpus of the LLM, raising concerns about potential data leakage and the possibility of retrieving answers from the memory of the LLM.",
    "500xCompressor explores prompt compression at high compression ratios while maintaining the compression length limit of ICAE (Li et al., 2024).",
    "Similar to ICAE, 500xCompressor employs trainable LoRA parameters (Gao et al., 2020a) in the encoder, while keeping the original LLM frozen in the decoder."
  ],
